statement:
\emph{Multiple Choice Question: Exactly ONE of the answers provided is
correct. There is no partial credit in this questions.}

A random variable $X$ can take on one of the values $\{1,3,5\}$ with
(discrete) probabilities $p(1) = 1/2$, $p(3) = 1/4$, $p(5)=1/4$. The
mean value of $X$ is then

\begin{description}
\itemsep1pt\parskip0pt\parsep0pt
\item[]
\emph{i.} $5/2$
\end{description}

\begin{description}
\itemsep1pt\parskip0pt\parsep0pt
\item[]
\emph{ii.} $9$
\end{description}

\begin{description}
\itemsep1pt\parskip0pt\parsep0pt
\item[]
\emph{iii.} $3$
\end{description}

\begin{description}
\itemsep1pt\parskip0pt\parsep0pt
\item[]
\emph{iv.} $2/5$
\end{description}

\begin{description}
\itemsep1pt\parskip0pt\parsep0pt
\item[]
\emph{v.} $1$
\end{description}
